  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align=center cellpadding='3' width='85%'>
  <tr><td class='spti2'>PLAYER JOURNAL</td></tr>  <tr><td class='db'><font class='dbti'>Epic Quest</font> - Ctiz </td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'> </td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>A couple weeks ago, my guild gathered all the monks that still needed to kill Eejag.  We had 3 groups there.  There were 4 monks that needed the scale including myself.  We killed Eejag until all 4 of us had scales.

4/12-13 -- My guild had a date in Fear.  We cleared it in just over 2 hours.  After the Fear raid, I got a Lvl 60 cleric, Lvl 60 warrior, 2 Lvl 57 monks and me, a Lvl 56 monk to head up to Sky to kill Gwan with me.  We killed two thunderspirits rather quickly and also wiped out the Thunderspirit princess.  Off to Noble Djorn island.  We all arrived in the windwill, one of the other monks who already had their epic showed me where Gwan was and advised me to pull very slowly.  I had heard all the problem with getting Gwan into the windmill and that he would path off of the island, etc....  So I handed in my scales, and Gwan spawned.  I told him I was prepared and he started attacking.  I took one step backwards and he took off, I thought he was going off the island, but it was just really bad pathing.  So it takes him a few seconds to get to me and I walk backwards into the Windmill with him beating on me all the way.  We dispatched him rather quickly and I got my breath of Gwan.

So we jump out of Sky and land in E Freeport.  We go to Dreadlands so we can head to Nurga to kill Trunt.  We entered Nurga and the Sleeping Ogre was not up.  So the rest of the group goes off and does other stuff, while I wait for the Sleeping Ogre to spawn.  About 2 hours after I arrived in Nurga, he spawned.  Within 30 minutes, I had to groups, everyone over lvl 54 and we killed Trunt rather easily.  

I head off to The Overthere to talk to the Astral Projection.  Had in Trunts head and I receive the eye, which is needed to spawn Deep, Vorash, and Xenevorash in Lake of Ill Omen.  It was quite late, when I had gotten the eye, and most of my guild had logged for the night.  We plan on killing Deep, Vorash and Xenevorash, sometime within the next few days.

4/14 - I logged on early in the morning to a warrior Guildmate yelling to the guild that Servilous is up in TT.  The guild gathers and we kill Servilous, but he does not drop the green scale.  After the death of Servilous, we headed to Lake of Ill Omen for my final battle.

After everyone arrives for the final battle, I hand in the item.  We had 4 groups there.  Vorash and Deep spawn and I take off running to the shore.  A druid was suppost to kite Deep around, while we dispatch Vorash, but Deep will not leave the fight.  We kill Vorash and start on Deep.  Once Deep was down to about 1/4 health remaining, I was told to the Xenevorash.  I run to the platform and he charged me and stunned me on first hit.  He did some serious damage really quick.  I was down to 1/2 health when stunned wore off.  Headed to shore and once at the beach he stunned me again.  Luckily for me, I was in healing range and received a heal from our cleric.  That aggroed Xenevorash to the rest of the group and we killed him with no deaths.  I looted my fang and off to Erudin.

I arrived in Tox Forest, and the guild was headed to The Hole to help a shaman kill his epic.  Well I got to Erudin entrance, and realized I only had one invis potion on me.  So I got above the entrance to Erudin, hit SNEAK and dropped down and headed to the zone with no aggro.  Took the teleported, conning everything around me.  Found the entrance to the Library and found Tomekeeper Dahl on the 2nd floor.  Handed in my item and received Dahl's reference.  I stood up, invised myself and ran to the druid ring.

I spend about 30 minutes getting a port out of Tox.  I got the port to Sro, so I could head to Timorous Deep.  Take the boat to the chessboard island and swim to the hidden oasis.  Once I make it all the way inside, I look near the huts, and there is no Lheao.  I run around the beach and there is no Lheao.  I look around for about 20 minutes and decide to petition.  After the petition, I decided to swim around and see if he is underwater.  Sure enough, he was underwater.  So I hail him and he is still giving out the quest.  So I hand him my RoWF and Dahl's reference and get the Celestial Book.  Once I have the Book in my inventory, I head to the Firepot room in Timorous Deep to get ported to Cabilis.  From Cabilis, I ran to TT to find Kaiaren.

Once in TT, the fake Kaiaren was at the entrance to the ruins to Old Sebilis.  I handed in the book and he started attacking me.  I FD him off and took off for the real Kaiaren, which is in the ruins by the lake.  Got there, handed in the book, went through the quest text.  Then I handed in my Demon Fang, and Celestial Fist Book and received my Celestial Fist.

That is my story on how I received my Celestial Fist.

Ctiz
Lvl 56 Iksar Master

</td></tr>
